The Judiciary Staff Union of Nigeria (JUSUN) has commiserated with President Muhammadu Buhari over the death of his Chief of staff (COS) Mallam Abba Kyari from covid-19 complications. The Union in a letter of condolence addressed to President Buhari, described late Kyari as a patriotic Nigerian who served the country until his death. The letter signed by the union President Comrade Marwan Mustapha further said the former Chief of staff died at a time the government of Nigeria needed him Most. The letter reads”On behalf of the National Executive Council (NEC) and members of Judiciary Staff Union of Nigeria (JUSUN), I write to condole you, the Government and people of the Federal Republic of Nigeria; over the demise of your Chief of Staff (COS), Dr. Abba Kyari, a patriot Nigerian and confidant who died due to complications from the dreaded corona virus. “This is indeed a very trying time for you, the people of Nigeria and the world in general as the deadly pandemic is ravaging the entire nations of the world and especially the global economy. “His death is no doubt an irreparable loss to you, his family, and the entire nation, even at a time he was needed mostly to complete the good and wonderful work your government has been doing to place the country on the path of enviable growth and development. “To say that his patriotic zeal for the country forced him to go to Germany in respect of a contractual agreement to improve our troubled electricity sector; where he probably contacted the disease that eventually led to his death, says the least of his unquantifiable love for Nigeria and her people. “We pray that Allah gives you and the members of his family the fortitude to bear the loss.” 